Challenges#
After going through key ideas and demos of building LLM-centered agents, I start to see a couple common limitations:

Component One: Planning#
A complicated task usually involves many steps. An agent needs to know what they are and plan ahead.
Task Decomposition#

Planning

Subgoal and decomposition: The agent breaks down large tasks into smaller, manageable subgoals, enabling efficient handling of complex tasks.
Reflection and refinement: The agent can do self-criticism and self-reflection over past actions, learn from mistakes and refine them for future steps, thereby improving the quality of final results.


Memory","ANSWER: To effectively manage complex tasks within an autonomous agent system, two essential components work alongside the central controller: Subgoal and decomposition, which breaks down larger tasks into smaller, manageable ones; and Reflection and refinement, allowing the agent to analyze its own performance, learn from errors, and improve future decisions. This combination enhances efficiency and overall success rate.","To effectively manage complex tasks within an autonomous agent system, two essential components work alongside the central controller: Subgoal and decomposition, which breaks down larger tasks into smaller, manageable ones; and Reflection and refinement, allowing the agent to analyze its own performance, learn from errors, and improve future decisions. This combination enhances efficiency and overall success rate."
