multi-qa-mpnet-base-dot-v1,high_overlap,512,100,5,mistralai/Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3,marketing,87,What are the main components that complement the central controller in an autonomous agent system?,"}
]
Challenges#
After going through key ideas and demos of building LLM-centered agents, I start to see a couple common limitations:

Component One: Planning#
A complicated task usually involves many steps. An agent needs to know what they are and plan ahead.
Task Decomposition#

Planning

Subgoal and decomposition: The agent breaks down large tasks into smaller, manageable subgoals, enabling efficient handling of complex tasks.
Reflection and refinement: The agent can do self-criticism and self-reflection over past actions, learn from mistakes and refine them for future steps, thereby improving the quality of final results.


Memory

== Overview ==

Proof-of-Concept Examples#
AutoGPT has drawn a lot of attention into the possibility of setting up autonomous agents with LLM as the main controller. It has quite a lot of reliability issues given the natural language interface, but nevertheless a cool proof-of-concept demo. A lot of code in AutoGPT is about format parsing.
Here is the system message used by AutoGPT, where {{...}} are user inputs:
You are {{ai-name}}, {{user-provided AI bot description}}.","Answer: To build an effective autonomous agent system, two essential components complement the central controller: Planning and Memory. Planning enables breaking down complex tasks into manageable subgoals and learning from past errors to improve performance. This capability leads to increased efficiency in managing challenging tasks. On the other hand, Memory ensures reliable communication between the agent and human users by understanding and interpreting instructions correctly. By focusing on these elements, we create more intuitive, dependable autonomous systems.","To build an effective autonomous agent system, two essential components complement the central controller: Planning and Memory. Planning enables breaking down complex tasks into manageable subgoals and learning from past errors to improve performance. This capability leads to increased efficiency in managing challenging tasks. On the other hand, Memory ensures reliable communication between the agent and human users by understanding and interpreting instructions correctly. By focusing on these elements, we create more intuitive, dependable autonomous systems."
