* Planning: Enables efficient handling of complex tasks by breaking down large tasks into smaller, manageable subgoals, and improves results through self-criticism and self-reflection.
* Memory: Short-term memory allows the agent to learn during interaction, while long-term memory enables retention and recall of extensive information over time.
