multi-qa-mpnet-base-dot-v1,v_small_context,128,0,3,mistralai/Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3,research,110,How does Neural Turing Machine (NTM) simulate the infinite memory characteristic of Turing machines?,"external memory storage. The memory mimics the Turing machine tape and the neural network controls the operation heads to read

Neural Turing Machine (NTM, Graves, Wayne & Danihelka, 2014) is a model architecture for coupling a neural network with

NTM contains two major components, a controller neural network and a memory bank.","RESPONSE:
The Neural Turing Machine (NTM) simulates the infinite memory characteristic of Turing machines by utilizing a memory bank as its secondary component. This memory bank acts like a Turing machine tape, where each location can store an arbitrary symbol from a predefined alphabet. The controller neural network manages the positioning of the operation head(s), allowing it to access different symbols within the memory bank during computation. This enables NTM to process sequences of data without limitations imposed by finite memory sizes, thus approximating the infinite memory feature found in traditional Turing machines.","The Neural Turing Machine (NTM) simulates the infinite memory characteristic of Turing machines by utilizing a memory bank as its secondary component. This memory bank acts like a Turing machine tape, where each location can store an arbitrary symbol from a predefined alphabet. The controller neural network manages the positioning of the operation head(s), allowing it to access different symbols within the memory bank during computation. This enables NTM to process sequences of data without limitations imposed by finite memory sizes, thus approximating the infinite memory feature found in traditional Turing machines."
