A large language model (LLM) is a language model trained with self-supervised machine learning on a vast amount of text, designed for natural language processing tasks, especially language generation. The largest and most capable LLMs are generative pre-trained transformers (GPTs) and provide the core capabilities of modern chatbots. LLMs can be fine-tuned for specific tasks or guided by prompt engineering. These models acquire predictive power regarding syntax, semantics, and ontologies inherent in human

A large language model (LLM) is a language model trained with self-supervised machine learning on a vast amount of text, designed for natural language processing tasks, especially language generation. The largest and most capable LLMs are generative pre-trained transformers (GPTs) and provide the core capabilities of modern chatbots. LLMs can be fine-tuned for specific tasks or guided by prompt engineering. These models acquire predictive power regarding syntax, semantics, and ontologies inherent in human","Based on the provided context, a Large Language Model (LLM) in the context of Natural Language Processing (NLP) tasks refers to a language model that has been trained with Self-Supervised Machine Learning on an extensive dataset of text. This type of model is primarily designed for language generation tasks within NLP. The largest and most capable LLMs are Generative Pre-Trained Transformers (GPTs), which serve as the foundation for modern chatbot functionality. They can also be further specialized through Fine-Tuning for particular tasks or by utilizing Prompt Engineering techniques. By doing so, these models develop predictive abilities related to syntax, semantics, and ontologies found within human communication patterns.","Based on the provided context, a Large Language Model (LLM) in the context of Natural Language Processing (NLP) tasks refers to a language model that has been trained with Self-Supervised Machine Learning on an extensive dataset of text. This type of model is primarily designed for language generation tasks within NLP. The largest and most capable LLMs are Generative Pre-Trained Transformers (GPTs), which serve as the foundation for modern chatbot functionality. They can also be further specialized through Fine-Tuning for particular tasks or by utilizing Prompt Engineering techniques. By doing so, these models develop predictive abilities related to syntax, semantics, and ontologies found within human communication patterns."
