HALO loss functions aim to incorporate human preferences and perception of language into the training process. They often utilize specific mathematical constructs like preference scores, calibrated sequence likelihood, or even reference point distributions. Examples of HALOs mentioned in the context include DPO and PPO (with certain modifications for offline use).

