from or write to the tape. However, the memory in NTM is finite, and thus it probably looks more like a “Neural von Neumann","In the given context, the Neural Turing Machine (NTM) doesn't directly simulate the infinite memory characteristic of Turing machines. Instead, it employs a finite memory bank that acts as an approximation. This memory bank serves as the equivalent of the Turing machine tape, but its size is limited compared to the theoretical unbounded nature of the Turing machine tape.

