Definition#
Now let’s define the attention mechanism introduced in NMT in a scientific way. Say, we have a source sequence $\mathbf{x}$ of length $n$ and try to output a target sequence $\mathbf{y}$ of length $m$:","ANSWER: In Neural Machine Translation (NMT), one significant challenge lies in processing long source sentences effectively due to vanishing gradients during backpropagation. To overcome this issue, the attention mechanism was introduced (as described in Bahdanau et al., 2015). This technique creates a series of connections between the input and output layers called soft alignments or scaled dot products, which allow the model to focus on relevant parts of the input while generating each element of the output sequence. Unlike traditional recurrent networks where only the final hidden state encodes the whole input, these shortcut connections enable parallel processing of entire sequences. By allowing the model to selectively attend to certain words within the source sentence, it can generate more accurate translations even when dealing with longer inputs.","In Neural Machine Translation (NMT), one significant challenge lies in processing long source sentences effectively due to vanishing gradients during backpropagation. To overcome this issue, the attention mechanism was introduced (as described in Bahdanau et al., 2015). This technique creates a series of connections between the input and output layers called soft alignments or scaled dot products, which allow the model to focus on relevant parts of the input while generating each element of the output sequence. Unlike traditional recurrent networks where only the final hidden state encodes the whole input, these shortcut connections enable parallel processing of entire sequences. By allowing the model to selectively attend to certain words within the source sentence, it can generate more accurate translations even when dealing with longer inputs."
