Growth of natural language questions – Over time, the per-
cent of queries submitted in the search bar that are expressed as a
natural language question (versus a keyword search) has increased
from 25% to 39%. (Fig. 2)
User feedback – We worried users wouldn’t give feedback if it
required multiple clicks, choosing from difficult-to-interpret cate-
gories, or typing explanations. But we also worried simple “thumbs-
up” or “thumbs down” feedback wouldn’t be fine-grained enough
to analyze the impact of iterative solution improvements. So, we
chose a 1-click interface with three options: “helpful”, “somewhat
helpful”, and “unhelpful”. We found that users give feedback less
than 1% of the time, and mostly for unhelpful answers. (Fig. 3)
