rb(y|x)","Answer: To apply the reparameterization of reward functions within the context of Plackett-Luce and Bradley-Terry models, several assumptions must hold true. Firstly, the reward functions should adhere to the Plackett-Luce or Bradley-Terry preference framework, meaning they depend solely on the differences of rewards between two completions. Secondly, the reward functions considered belong to the same equivalence class defined by having equal differences due to a specific function f. Lastly, the reparameterized reward function r(x, y) = β log π(y|x) / πref(y|x) must result in a valid distribution, ensuring probabilities are positive and sum to 1.","To apply the reparameterization of reward functions within the context of Plackett-Luce and Bradley-Terry models, several assumptions must hold true. Firstly, the reward functions should adhere to the Plackett-Luce or Bradley-Terry preference framework, meaning they depend solely on the differences of rewards between two completions. Secondly, the reward functions considered belong to the same equivalence class defined by having equal differences due to a specific function f. Lastly, the reparameterized reward function r(x, y) = β log π(y|x) / πref(y|x) must result in a valid distribution, ensuring probabilities are positive and sum to 1."
