In a nutshell, attention in deep learning can be broadly interpreted as a vector of importance weights: in order to predict or infer one element, such as a pixel in an image or a word in a sentence, we estimate using the attention vector how strongly it","ANSWER: The attention mechanism addresses the challenge of processing long source sentences in Neural Machine Translation (NMT), specifically the issue of memory and maintaining meaningful context throughout the model. By creating a vector of importance weights, also known as soft alignment, the attention mechanism enables the model to selectively focus on relevant parts of the input during prediction or inference. This approach resolves the vanishing gradient problem often encountered when dealing with longer sequences. Essentially, instead of relying solely on the final hidden state from the encoder, the attention mechanism generates a weighted sum of multiple hidden states to better capture the meaning of the source sentence.","The attention mechanism addresses the challenge of processing long source sentences in Neural Machine Translation (NMT), specifically the issue of memory and maintaining meaningful context throughout the model. By creating a vector of importance weights, also known as soft alignment, the attention mechanism enables the model to selectively focus on relevant parts of the input during prediction or inference. This approach resolves the vanishing gradient problem often encountered when dealing with longer sequences. Essentially, instead of relying solely on the final hidden state from the encoder, the attention mechanism generates a weighted sum of multiple hidden states to better capture the meaning of the source sentence."
