instructions, improves their downstream performance on held-out tasks, both in the zero-shot and
few-shot settings.
There is also a related line of work on instruction following for navigation, where models are trained","Answer: Based on the context, fine-tuning a pre-trained Language Model (LLM) is a common approach to improve certain capacities of the model such as instruction following. During the fine-tuning phase, introducing new knowledge is challenging but unavoidable. This process allows the model to absorb domain-specific knowledge and become more accurate and relevant in its responses. However, when fine-tuning with Question Answering (QA) data, there might be concerns due to overlaps between questions in the training and test sets in some public QA datasets. This overlap could potentially bias the model towards the learned patterns rather than generalizing well. To mitigate these issues, techniques like adversarial learning, filtering the pretraining data, or hybrid approaches combining multiple strategies might be employed. These tactics aim to enhance factors like explain","Based on the context, fine-tuning a pre-trained Language Model (LLM) is a common approach to improve certain capacities of the model such as instruction following. During the fine-tuning phase, introducing new knowledge is challenging but unavoidable. This process allows the model to absorb domain-specific knowledge and become more accurate and relevant in its responses. However, when fine-tuning with Question Answering (QA) data, there might be concerns due to overlaps between questions in the training and test sets in some public QA datasets. This overlap could potentially bias the model towards the learned patterns rather than generalizing well. To mitigate these issues, techniques like adversarial learning, filtering the pretraining data, or hybrid approaches combining multiple strategies might be employed. These tactics aim to enhance factors like explain"
