To elaborate further, HALOs like DPO (Discounted Probability of Overestimation) and PPO (Proximal Policy Optimization) are defined mathematically in terms of human value functions and reference points, whereas a non-HALO like SLiC does not adhere to these properties. Specifically, a HALO should satisfy certain conditions outlined in Definition 3.4 in the context, while SLiC fails to meet them.

